properties.NAME: Alabama
properties.CHANGE: MARION's overlap of the state of Mississippi and TUSCALOOSA's overlap of the state of Mississippi ended.

properties.NAME: Arkansas
properties.CHANGE: Survey of boundary between the Republic of Texas and the United States began. MILLER (original) officially became extinct and LAFAYETTE was eliminated from Texas when Texas claims to the area were upheld.

properties.NAME: Arizona Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created  Arizona Territory from the western portion of New Mexico Territory and a part of present Nevada.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 12, ch. 56[1863]/pp. 664-665; Ariz. Terr. Laws 1864, 1st assy./ pp. vii-viii; Van Zandt, 162)

properties.NAME: California
properties.CHANGE: The state of California was admitted to the Union.

properties.NAME: Colorado Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Colorado Territory from Nebraska, New Mexico, and Utah Territories, and from the former Kansas Territory.

properties.NAME: Connecticut
properties.CHANGE: HARTFORD lost part of the town of Southwick (the "Southwick Jog") to HAMPSHIRE (Mass.) when the state boundary was adjusted.

properties.NAME: District of Columbia
properties.CHANGE: The federal government retroceded to Virginia all of the District of Columbia west of the Potomac River, including all of ALEXANDRIA (now ARLINGTON, Va.). ALEXANDRIA eliminated from the District of Columbia.

properties.NAME: Delaware
properties.CHANGE: The three Lower Counties, of KENT, NEW CASTLE, and SUSSEX became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The name Delaware was formally adopted on 20 September 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Dakota Territory
properties.CHANGE: Dakota Territory gained from Idaho Territory; included most of present Wyoming and a small area of about two square miles in present Montana that had been part of MADISON (Mont.).

properties.NAME: Florida
properties.CHANGE: The state of Florida was created from Florida Territory, with boundaries the same as those set in 1822; Florida Territory eliminated.

properties.NAME: Georgia
properties.CHANGE: Georgia ceded to the United States much of present Mississippi and Alabama. This area became unorganized federal territory and Georgia Western Lands were eliminated.

properties.NAME: Iowa
properties.CHANGE: The state of Iowa was created from Iowa Territory; Iowa Territory eliminated.

properties.NAME: Idaho Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Montana Territory from Idaho Territory with boundaries identical to the state of Montana; Dakota Territory gained most of present Wyoming from Idaho Territory.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 13, ch. 95 [1864], sec. 1/pp. 85-92 and sec. 18/p. 92; Sanders, Helen F., 1:329; Van Zandt, 134-136, 145, 156-157)

properties.NAME: Illinois
properties.CHANGE: The state of Illinois was created from Illinois Territory; Illinois Territory eliminated.

properties.NAME: Indiana
properties.CHANGE: The state of Indiana was created from Indiana Territory and small parts of Illinois and Michigan Territories.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 3, ch. 57 [1816], secs. 1-2/p. 289 and res. 1 [1816]/p. 399; Van Zandt, 115)

properties.NAME: Indian Territory
properties.CHANGE: Indian Territory gained from Arkansas Territory when the Treaty of Washington between the United States and Choctaw Indians definitively established the eastern line of the Choctaw Cession and affirmed Choctaw control of the area west of the line.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 7, p. 311; Gabler, 37-39; Royce, 720-721; Van Zandt, 119)

properties.NAME: Kansas
properties.CHANGE: The state of Kansas was created from Kansas Territory; Kansas Territory eliminated.

properties.NAME: Kentucky
properties.CHANGE: ROBERTSON (Tenn.) and SUMNER (Tenn.) gained from SIMPSON (Ky.) when surveyors re-marking the Kentucky-Tennessee boundary acted without authority and shifted the line around two small parcels.

properties.NAME: Louisiana
properties.CHANGE: The State of Louisiana was created from Orleans Territory; Orleans Territory eliminated.

properties.NAME: Massachusetts
properties.CHANGE: BRISTOL gained from NEWPORT (R.I.) and lost to PROVIDENCE (R.I.) when Massachusetts and Rhode Island implemented the U.S. Supreme Court settlement (31 December 1861) of their boundary to the Atlantic Ocean.
properties.CITATION: (Bayles, Providence, 1:29; R.I. Acts 1861, ch. 379/pp. 4-6; Ullman, 83-84; Van Zandt, 68)

properties.NAME: Maryland
properties.CHANGE: The United States created an unnamed district from land ceded by Maryland and Virginia to be the seat of national government.

properties.NAME: Maine
properties.CHANGE: Maine was separated from Massachusetts and admitted to the Union.

properties.NAME: Michigan
properties.CHANGE: The state of Michigan was created from Michigan Territory; boundary dispute with Ohio over the strip running from Indiana to Lake Erie was settled in favor of Ohio; Michigan Territory eliminated.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 5, ch. 99 [1836], secs. 1-2/p. 49 and ch. 6 [1837]/p. 144; Van Zandt, 127)

properties.NAME: Minnesota
properties.CHANGE: The state of Minnesota was created from Minnesota Territory;  Minnesota Territory eliminated. The remainder of Minnesota Territory (west of the present state boundary) became unorganized federal territory.

properties.NAME: Missouri
properties.CHANGE: U.S. Supreme Court settled boundary dispute between Iowa and Missouri by rejecting both states' claims, choosing instead the commonly accepted boundary before the dispute arose and the present boundary between the two states.

properties.NAME: Mississippi
properties.CHANGE: Surveyors demarcated the southern segment of the Alabama-Mississippi line, fixing the end point ten miles east of the mouth of the Pascagoula River.

properties.NAME: Montana Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Montana Territory from Idaho Territory; boundaries were identical to the state of Montana, except for a small area of about two square miles (formerly part of MADISON) that became part of Dakota Territory.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 13, ch. 95 [1864], sec. 1/pp. 85-92; Sanders, Helen F., 1:329; Van Zandt, 145)

properties.NAME: North Carolina
properties.CHANGE: Congress accepted North Carolina's cession of its western lands (i.e. present Tennessee).

properties.NAME: Nebraska Territory
properties.CHANGE: Nebraska Territory lost the area in present Wyoming to creation of Idaho Territory.

properties.NAME: New Hampshire
properties.CHANGE: New Hampshire became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: New Jersey
properties.CHANGE: New Jersey became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: New Mexico Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Arizona Territory from New Mexico Territory.

properties.NAME: Nevada
properties.CHANGE: The state of Nevada was created from Nevada Territory and admitted to the Union by presidential proclamation.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 13, ch. 36[1864]/pp. 30-32 and proc. 22/p. 749; Van Zandt, 158-160)

properties.NAME: New York
properties.CHANGE: New York acquired the southwestern corner of Massachusetts (Boston Corner).

properties.NAME: Ohio
properties.CHANGE: The state of Ohio was created from the Northwest Territory and Indiana Territory.
properties.CITATION: (Ind. Terr., Exec. Journal, 114-115; Pence and Armstrong, 218; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 40 [1802], secs. 1-3/pp. 173-174; Van Zandt, 112)

properties.NAME: Oregon
properties.CHANGE: The state of Oregon was created from Oregon Territory; Oregon Territory eliminated.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 11, ch. 33[1859], secs. 1-2/pp. 383-384; Ore. Laws 1860, 1st reg. sess., pp. 28-30)

properties.NAME: Pennsylvania
properties.CHANGE: Pennsylvania purchased from the federal government the Erie Triangle, a small area immediately north of Pennsylvania and west of New York, giving Pennsylvania an outlet to Lake Erie.

properties.NAME: Rhode Island
properties.CHANGE: NEWPORT lost to BRISTOL (Mass.) and PROVIDENCE gained from BRISTOL (Mass.) when Massachusetts and Rhode Island implemented the U. S. Supreme Court settlement (31 December 1861) of their boundary to the Atlantic Ocean.
properties.CITATION: (Bayles, Providence, 1:29; R.I. Acts and Resolves, 1861, ch. 379, sec. 2/p. 4; Ullman, 83-84; Van Zandt, 68)

properties.NAME: South Carolina
properties.CHANGE: South Carolina became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Tennessee
properties.CHANGE: ROBERTSON (Tenn.) and SUMNER (Tenn.) gained from SIMPSON (Ky.) when surveyors remarking the Kentucky-Tennessee boundary acted without authority and shifted the line around two small parcels.

properties.NAME: Texas
properties.CHANGE: State of Texas sold land in present Colorado, Kansas, New Mexico, Oklahoma, and Wyoming to the United States.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 9, ch. 49 [1850]/pp. 446-452 and appendix, sec. 10/pp. 1005-1006; Texas Laws 1850, 3d leg., 3d sess., ch. 2/p. 4; Van Zandt, 122)

properties.NAME: Unorg. Fed. Terr.
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Dakota Territory from Nebraska Territory and Unorganized Federal Territory.
properties.CITATION: (Dak. Terr. Laws 1862, 1st sess., pp. 21-28; U.S. Stat., vol. 12, ch. 86[1861]/pp. 239-244; Van Zandt, 134, 136-137)

properties.NAME: Utah Territory
properties.CHANGE: Nevada Territory gained from Utah Territory.

properties.NAME: Virginia
properties.CHANGE: The state of Virginia lost JEFFERSON (W.Va.) to West Virginia.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Rpts., 78:39 [Wallace, vol. 11]; U.S. Stat., vol. 14, res. 12[1866]/p. 350; W.Va. Acts 1863, 1st sess., ch. 90, sec. 1/pp. 103-105)

properties.NAME: Vermont
properties.CHANGE: The state of Vermont was admitted to the Union. The boundary with New York was settled by a joint commission before statehood.

properties.NAME: Washington Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Idaho Territory from Dakota, Nebraska, and Washington Territories.

properties.NAME: Wisconsin
properties.CHANGE: The state of Wisconsin was created from Wisconsin Territory. The area in present Minnesota between the Mississippi River and the state of Wisconsin continued as de facto Wisconsin Territory until the creation of Minnesota Territory on 3 March 1849.

properties.NAME: West Virginia
properties.CHANGE: JEFFERSON was separated from Virginia and became a county in the state of West Virginia.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Rpts., 78:39 [Wallace, vol. 11]; U.S. Stat., vol. 14, res. 12 [1866]/ p. 350; W.Va. Acts 1863, 1st sess., ch. 90, sec. 1/pp. 103-105)
